 compatibility issues with generated code.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"jackrabbit-webdav declares javax.servlet:servlet-api as a provided dependency, and key server/io WebDAV classes expose javax.servlet request/response types, so meaningful coverage of the servlet-facing API needs that API on the test compile classpath.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"javax.servlet:servlet-api:2.3\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The 2.0-beta4 POM inherits servlet-api 2.3 as a provided dependency; Gradle will not bring it transitively for tests, but classes such as AbstractWebdavServlet, InputContextImpl, OutputContextImpl, WebdavRequestImpl, and WebdavResponseImpl reference javax.servlet types.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker image, external WebDAV server, environment variable, or system property appears necessary. Prefer in-memory XML/protocol object tests and lightweight mocks/stubs for servlet request and response objects; use javax.servlet APIs, not jakarta.servlet.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The reported native-image run failure is likely a metadata/runtime behavior issue rather than missing infrastructure setup, so this preparation may not by itself fix the failing tests.\",\n    \"The servlet API is old and provided-scoped in the upstream artifact; using newer jakarta.servlet imports would be incompatible with this library version.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0d6b82fb20080e12016a422227d8388197ae4e3697fe81b938\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3624, "output": 827, "cacheRead": 16896, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 21347, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782719005633, "responseId": "resp_0d6b82fb20080e